<text top="82" left="83" width="677" height="54" font="1">Who is The Man In The Middle?</text>
<text top="166" left="53" width="939" height="40" font="2">When we send data across a network outside our physical </text>
<text top="209" left="53" width="914" height="40" font="2">control (untrusted Ethernet, all WiFi, all Mobile Data, The </text>
<text top="253" left="53" width="913" height="40" font="2">Internet) we must assume that a man in the middle can…</text>
<text top="296" left="53" width="961" height="40" font="2">• <b>View </b>the messages content so read personal information </text>
<text top="339" left="94" width="118" height="40" font="2">in them</text>
<text top="382" left="53" width="853" height="40" font="2">• <b>Intercept </b>the messages to stop them reaching the </text>
<text top="425" left="94" width="295" height="40" font="2">intended recipient </text>
<text top="469" left="53" width="923" height="40" font="2">• <b>Repeat </b>the messages to try to gain access to a secure </text>
<text top="512" left="94" width="114" height="40" font="2">system</text>
</page>
