<text top="82" left="83" width="762" height="54" font="1">Cryptography – Classic Approaches</text>
<text top="153" left="49" width="922" height="34" font="4">How do we address this problem? Our ideas have evolved quite a lot </text>
<text top="189" left="49" width="123" height="34" font="4">over time</text>
<text top="261" left="49" width="946" height="34" font="5"><i><b>Cryptography </b></i>– a form of secret writing, any technique to disguise the </text>
<text top="297" left="49" width="814" height="34" font="4">meaning of a word to those who don’t know how to interpret it</text>
<text top="366" left="49" width="676" height="34" font="5"><i><b>Transposition cyp</b></i><b>hers </b>– hello world = ehlol owrdl</text>
<text top="402" left="49" width="795" height="34" font="4">• Swap the ordering of letters around in some fixed pattern</text>
<text top="470" left="49" width="692" height="34" font="5"><i><b>Substitution Cyphers </b></i>– hello world = ifmmp xpsme</text>
<text top="506" left="49" width="905" height="34" font="4">• Take a letter and replace it with another letter, so a becomes z, b </text>
<text top="542" left="90" width="537" height="34" font="4">becomes y, c becomes x, d becomes…..</text>
</page>
